[normal]6.[bold]              [bold]Access to banking in rural communities[bold]&#xa0;[bold]6.1
[normal]              
[normal]The 
[normal]rationalisation
[normal] of the branch networks of the four major banks in Nor
[normal]thern Ireland raises questions about access to banking facilities in rural communities. While 
[normal]Danske
[normal] Bank has implemented the most d
[normal]ramatic reduction 
[normal]programme
[normal], 
[normal]the other banks are 
[normal]to be
[normal] developing similar strategies involving a concentration of face-to-fa
[normal]ce banking operations in fewer locations while seeking to increase the use of electronic banking services.
[normal] S
[normal]ome institutions may be tempted to accelerate the closure of branches 
[normal]to push
[normal] the adoption of electronic bank
[normal]ing by customers rather than 
[normal]allow cust
[normal]omers to move at their own pace or even retain the option of face-to-face interaction.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]6.
[normal]2
[normal]              
